PREREGISTRATION: D3_EGFR_MUTANT_NSCLC_v1
=========================================
Date: 2026-06-06
Experiment: D3_EGFR_MUTANT_NSCLC
Network: examples/egfr_nsclc_signaling.json
Version: v1
Cancer type: NSCLC (EGFR-mutant; L858R or exon-19 deletion)
Driver: EGFR activating point mutation (constitutive kinase, no ligand needed)
Structural regime tested: KRAS-like ODS vs CLASS 6b driver-addiction vs CLASS 7 decoupling

FILTER
------
Cancer lineage: NSCLC
CRISPR dependency: EGFR Chronos < -0.5 (column: "EGFR (1956)")
Expected EGFR-dependent lines: HCC827, PC9, HCC4006, H3255 (all EGFR L858R or del19)
Exclusions: CDK4/6 inhibitors (cytostatic class), BET/JQ1 (potency gap class)

PERTURBATION RESULTS
--------------------
Baseline r(physical_interaction, coexpression_cancer) = 0.7472
Method: irdme perturb examples/egfr_nsclc_signaling.json --layer-a physical_interaction --layer-b coexpression_cancer
Layers: physical_interaction vs coexpression_cancer

Protein nodes (biologically meaningful — 15 nodes):
  EGFR:   delta_r = -0.0009  ANCHOR (near-neutral; 11 edges; key test node)
  GRB2:   delta_r = +0.0351  DAMPER  (upstream adaptor)
  SOS1:   delta_r = +0.0747  DAMPER  (strongest damper; upstream GEF)
  RAS:    delta_r = +0.0537  DAMPER  (RAS relay; WT in EGFR-mut NSCLC)
  BRAF:   delta_r = -0.0113  ANCHOR  (WT BRAF; structural relay)
  MEK1:   delta_r = +0.0040  DAMPER  (testable: trametinib)
  ERK1:   delta_r = -0.0822  ANCHOR  (strongest anchor; no direct PRISM inhibitor)
  MYC:    delta_r = -0.0222  ANCHOR  (transcriptional output)
  PI3K:   delta_r = -0.0151  ANCHOR  (testable: copanlisib)
  PTEN:   delta_r = +0.0050  DAMPER  (tumor suppressor; no drug)
  AKT1:   delta_r = -0.0211  ANCHOR  (testable: MK-2206)
  mTOR:   delta_r = +0.0047  DAMPER  (testable: everolimus)
  JAK2:   delta_r = -0.0294  ANCHOR  (EGFR-JAK2 transactivation arm)
  STAT3:  delta_r = -0.0159  ANCHOR  (downstream of JAK2)
  TP53:   delta_r = +0.0050  DAMPER  (tumor suppressor; no drug)

Drug nodes (structural artifact — zero-degree in tested layers):
  All 8 drug nodes show delta_r = -0.0102 (zero-degree node removal artifact)
  Drug-node delta_r values are NOT used for ODS hypothesis testing.

KEY STRUCTURAL OBSERVATION:
  EGFR (primary driver, 11 edges) is the most structurally NEUTRAL testable node.
  Despite having the highest edge count, removal barely changes cross-layer correlation.
  SOS1/RAS/GRB2 (upstream adaptors) are the strongest dampers.
  ERK1 (downstream effector) is the strongest anchor.
  This is structurally distinct from BRAF V600E melanoma where the driver (BRAF)
  was a clear anchor (-0.0655) and KRAS-cancers where key effectors are dampers.

TESTABLE NODES (drug-covered, exclusions applied)
-------------------------------------------------
  AKT1:  delta_r = -0.0211  ANCHOR  drugs: MK-2206
  PI3K:  delta_r = -0.0151  ANCHOR  drugs: copanlisib
  EGFR:  delta_r = -0.0009  ANCHOR  drugs: erlotinib, gefitinib, afatinib, osimertinib*
  MEK1:  delta_r = +0.0040  DAMPER  drugs: trametinib
  mTOR:  delta_r = +0.0047  DAMPER  drugs: everolimus
  (*osimertinib may not be in PRISM secondary screen; include if present)

ODS REGIME PREDICTION (if H1 confirmed):
  Most effective: MEK1(trametinib) ≈ mTOR(everolimus)
  Least effective: AKT1(MK-2206) > PI3K(copanlisib) > EGFR(erlotinib/gefitinib)

CLASS 6b PREDICTION (if H2 confirmed):
  Most effective: AKT1(MK-2206) > PI3K(copanlisib) > EGFR TKIs
  Least effective: MEK1(trametinib) ≈ mTOR(everolimus)

CLASS 7 PREDICTION (if H3 confirmed):
  EGFR TKIs are most effective (mean LFC <= -0.5) despite EGFR being near-neutral.
  Spearman r between delta_r and LFC is non-significant.
  Interpretation: oncogenic driver addiction completely decouples topology from efficacy.

HYPOTHESES
----------
H1_ODS_REGIME:
  Spearman r(target delta_r, mean LFC in EGFR-dep NSCLC lines) < -0.40 AND p < 0.05
  Verdict rule: CONFIRMED if Spearman r < -0.40 AND p < 0.05; DENIED otherwise

H2_DRIVER_ADDICTION_CLASS6b:
  Spearman r(target delta_r, mean LFC) > +0.40 AND p < 0.05
  Verdict rule: CONFIRMED if Spearman r > +0.40 AND p < 0.05; DENIED otherwise

H3_ONCOGENIC_DECOUPLING:
  EGFR TKIs (erlotinib, gefitinib, afatinib) achieve mean LFC <= -0.5 in EGFR-dep lines AND |Spearman r| < 0.40 (non-significant topology-efficacy correlation)
  Verdict rule: CONFIRMED if mean(erlotinib/gefitinib/afatinib LFC) <= -0.5 AND -0.40 < Spearman r < +0.40; DENIED otherwise

H4_EGFR_VS_AKT1:
  mean(EGFR TKI LFC) < mean(AKT1 inhibitor LFC) — i.e., EGFR inhibitors more effective than AKT1 inhibitors
  Verdict rule: CONFIRMED if mean(erlotinib LFC, gefitinib LFC, afatinib LFC) < MK-2206_LFC

REGIME CLASSIFICATION MATRIX
-----------------------------
ODS (KRAS-like):          H1 CONFIRMED, H2 DENIED, H3 DENIED
CLASS 6b (driver-addict): H1 DENIED, H2 CONFIRMED, H3 DENIED
CLASS 7 (decoupled):      H1 DENIED, H2 DENIED, H3 CONFIRMED
Mixed/unclear:             Any other combination

ANALYSIS PLAN
-------------
1. Load PRISM secondary screen replicate-collapsed LFC data
2. Filter NSCLC lines with EGFR Chronos < -0.5 in DepMap 26Q1 CRISPR data
3. For each testable drug: compute mean LFC across EGFR-dependent NSCLC lines
4. Map drug → target delta_r (protein target, not drug node delta_r)
5. Compute Spearman r(target delta_r, mean drug LFC) across 5 testable targets
6. Assess H1/H2/H3/H4 verdicts per rules above
7. Classify regime using matrix above

DATA SOURCES
------------
PRISM Secondary: primary-screen-replicate-collapsed-logfold-change.csv
CRISPR: CRISPRGeneEffect.csv (DepMap 26Q1)
Cell line metadata: Model.csv (DepMap 26Q1)

